real homeowners and protect their right to build assets and wealth over time."This is the only way to break the cycle of
inter-generational poverty that Apartheid has left us," Maimane added.Maimane suggested that the model pursued by the Economic
Freedom Fighters (EFF) would strip all property owners of their property."White and black
South Africans alike would lose everything.""We reject the suggestion that people cannot own
property or should be permanent tenants of an all-powerful state," Maimane said.However, Maimane highlighted that the DA is the only party
in South Africa that has focused on changing ownership of urban land, by making
sure that beneficiaries of state subsidised housing have full ownership titles to their homes.Maimane further added that the Constitution also makes it
clear that property does not only refer to land."The model pursued by the EFF would strip all property
owners of their property - white and black South Africans alike would lose
everything.Homeowners would be stripped of their homes, business owners
